          &lt;p class=&quot;md-end-block md-p&quot;&gt;In this episode of the Epigenetics Podcast, we caught up with Nick Pervolarakis from Active Motif to talk about bioinformatic analysis in epigenetics research.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;md-end-block md-p md-focus&quot;&gt;While many “bench scientists” are familiar with the workflows of ChIP-Seq, ATAC-Seq and CUT&amp;Tag, and even the preparation and analysis of the libraries, the steps between sequencing and fully analyzed data is sometimes thought of as a mystery known only to bioinformatic experts. Most of us have some understanding that the raw data is usually in a file format called a FASTQ. But how do we get from FASTQ files to peaks on a genome browser? This Podcast Episode will provide a peek behind the curtain of the informatic analysis we perform at Active Motif, as part of our end-to-end epigenetic services.&lt;/p&gt;
