          &lt;p lang=&quot;en-us&quot; style=&quot;margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;&quot; xml:lang=&quot;en-us&quot;&gt;In this episode of the Epigenetics Podcast, we caught up with Dr. Christine Cucinotta and Dr. Melvin Noe Gonzalez to talk about how they brought the #fragilenucleosome seminar series and Discord channel to life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p lang=&quot;en-us&quot; style=&quot;margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;&quot; xml:lang=&quot;en-us&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p lang=&quot;en-us&quot; style=&quot;margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;&quot; xml:lang=&quot;en-us&quot;&gt;Christine Cucinotta and Melvin Noe Gonzales are part of the organizing committee of the independent scientific community &quot;Fragile Nucleosome.&quot; This community consists of a Discord channel with more than 1,000 members, a biweekly seminar series, a mentoring program, and a journal club series. The Fragile Nucleosome is organized exclusively by early-career scientists, without external sponsors or under the roof of a single graduate program or university.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p lang=&quot;en-us&quot; style=&quot;margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;&quot; xml:lang=&quot;en-us&quot;&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
